      "shortCode": "DWRbMyBiZ1h",
      "caption": "Drop “REGRET” and I’ll send it over.\nMost people make their biggest decisions when they’re the most emotional.\nJeff Bezos developed something called the Regret Minimization Framework before he quit his Wall Street job to start Amazon. \nIt comes down to three questions.\n\n1. Is this reversible? Most scary decisions feel permanent, yet rarely are. If it doesn’t work, can you recover? Typically, the answer is yes.\n\n2. Will you regret not trying? Project yourself to age 80 and look back. Sounds trite, but regret is worse than failure.\n\n3. Are you deciding from fear or from clarity?\n\nI’ve helped dozens of people buy and sell 7 and 8-figure businesses. Some of the biggest decisions of their lives. The ones who get it right have a framework (mental model) that gets them out of their own head before they decide.\n\nComment REGRET and I’ll DM you the three questions in a format you can actually use.",
